description: NEXT-ChemX Corporation owns a novel membrane-based ion extraction technology that mimics biophysical processes in nature to separate low concentrations of ions from liquid and extract them into concentrated form. Its technology is designated as NCX and applied for lithium extraction, vegetable oil refining, radioactive ion extraction, metal ions extraction, and desalination. The company was formerly known as AllyMe Group, Inc. and changed its name to NEXT-ChemX Corporation in July 2021. NEXT-ChemX Corporation was incorporated in 2014 and is based in Austin, Texas.
